    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.20/10–1148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 11, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gama1">Gama</gloss> 1307. Ur comments and recommendations
                    requested re Grk memo Sept 30 (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                        1969-<note n="1" xml:id="d116fn1">Dated October 1, <ref target="#pg_155">p.
                            155</ref>.</note>) copy just received but not yet studied ur
                    recommendation whether <gloss target="#t_GNA1">GNA</gloss> should be authorized
                    continue Particular urgency, light penultimate para War <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss> 1908 Sept 30, is 10,000 of 15,000 overstrength scheduled for
                    reduction Oct 20.</p>
                <pb facs="0178" n="158" xml:id="pg_158"/>
                <p>This connection, Dept recommends possibility extending military service beyond 24
                    months be thoroughly explored as means retaining trained personnel and
                    eliminating necessity 10,000 spaces for replacement system. In Dept’s view 24
                    months tour duty expensive and inappropriate under present emergency, and Dept
                    Army considers it waste trained manpower.</p>
                <p>Dept addressing letter to Sec Defense requesting concurrence in allotment
                    additional $25,000,000 to Turkey as approved <gloss target="#t_Amag2"
                        >Amag</gloss> 1581.<note n="2" xml:id="d116fn2">Dated September 29, <ref
                            target="#pg_152">p. 152</ref>.</note> Further allotments between Greece
                    and Turkey from remaining $25,000,000 being deferred pending developments
                    guerrilla war and receipt detailed presentation requirements which Army
                    requesting from Van Fleet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
